public abstract class InitializableBean<B,​P extends BeanInitParams>
extends AnchorBean<B>

A bean that must be initialized with some parameters before being used.

    • initRecursiveWithInitializer

      public void initRecursiveWithInitializer​(PropertyInitializer<?> pi, Logger logger) throws InitException
      Initializes the bean and recursively all contained beans (who have compatible initialization requirements)

      The correct initialization parameters are found for each bean via the pi parameter;

      Parameters:
      pi - the property-initializer to use
      logger - logger
      Throws:
      InitException - if the initialization fails, including if correct initialization-parameters cannot be derived

    • initRecursive

      public void initRecursive​(P params, Logger logger) throws InitException
      Inits this object, and all children objects, so long as they have P Once a Bean doesn't have P, the children are not evaluated
      Parameters:
      params - init-params
      logger - logger
      Throws:
      InitException - if the initialization fails
